</span></span></code></pre></div><h2 id="tags-and-priorities">Tags and Priorities</h2>
<p><img src="https://bledley.xyz/2025-06-25-how-i-use-org-mode-part-one/org-part-one-2.png" alt="Image 2"></p>
<p>I try to keep my tags for these todo&rsquo;s quite limited but the first area I think about it priority. Priorities are a little odd in org. By default it&rsquo;s a system where you can mark things as A,B,C priority. When searching for tasks every un-prioritised todo defaults to B which I&rsquo;m not keen on. One approach we can take to deal with that is to give every single task an A,B or C priority. Another way is a shift in thinking - sometimes I just think of it as the next 3 things I&rsquo;m going to do.. Do A, then B, then C. These priorities are set very easily with shift up and down.</p>
<p><img src="https://bledley.xyz/2025-06-25-how-i-use-org-mode-part-one/org-part-one-3.png" alt="Image 3"></p>
