</span></span></code></pre></div><p>These are my current tags I use for todos and fleeting thoughts. The ones beginning with <em>@</em> symbol are contexts. So, say I am working on domestic tasks around the house I can filter things down by searching for the <em>@home</em> tag. If I&rsquo;m working at my computer (system) I can pull up the <em>@sys</em> tagged tasks.</p>
<h2 id="org-capture-templates">Org capture templates</h2>
<p><img src="https://bledley.xyz/2025-06-25-how-i-use-org-mode-part-one/org-part-one-4.png" alt="Image 4"></p>
<p>Capturing new tasks is fast and easy using org-capture-templates. A dialogue for more specific org-capture will pop up with <em>&lsquo;C-c-c&rsquo; or F6</em></p>
<p>The options I&rsquo;m presented with there are;</p>
<p><strong>Todo (t)</strong></p>
<p><em>(Nested beneath t)</em></p>
<p><strong>-(p) Personal</strong> - add a new todo to <em>per.org</em> under the heading <em>&ldquo;INBOX:&rdquo;</em></p>
<p><strong>-(n) NA</strong> - add a new todo to <em>na.org</em> under the heading <em>&ldquo;INBOX:&rdquo;</em></p>
<p><strong>-(w) Work</strong> - add a new todo to <em>work.org</em> under the heading <em>&ldquo;INBOX:&rdquo;</em></p>
<p><strong>-(d) Done</strong> - add some task immediately with DONE status to <em>archive.org</em>. This is for things that come up and get completed that are not already in the system. By logging these they show the time they got completed on agenda views.</p>
<p><strong>Event (e)</strong> - add an entry to <em>event.org</em>. This file is synced with org-cal-dav so appointments show up everywhere I access my calendar. They are headlines without a todo status but have a <em>SCHEDULED</em> date stamp.</p>
<p><strong>Watch (w)</strong></p>
<p><em>(Nested beneath w)</em></p>
<p><strong>-(t) To Watch</strong> - films or shows I want to watch added to <em>watch.org</em></p>
<p><strong>-(d) Watched</strong> - when I watch something it gets logged as done with timestamp that shows on agenda views</p>
<p><strong>Planning (p)</strong></p>
<p><em>(Nested beneath p)</em></p>
<p><strong>-(p) Day Plan</strong> - add a quick checklist to my <em>log.org</em> (Primary Objectives for the day)</p>
<p><strong>-(r) End of day review</strong> - A few questions for EOD, What did I get done? what will I do next? etc. I don&rsquo;t use this as often as I should. I tend to use the following more consistently.</p>
<p><strong>-(w) End of week review</strong> - Same as above but with regards to the whole week. After a review of what I got done this becomes a plan for the next week as it has a prompt &ldquo;What&rsquo;s next?&rdquo;.</p>
