</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">14</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">15</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;td&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Óöú Done&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">entry</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/archive.org&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">16</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/tpl/tpl-done.txt&#34;</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">17</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">18</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;e&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Ôâ± Event&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">entry</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/events.org&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">19</span><span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;* %? \n %^t&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">20</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;w&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Ó´ô Watch&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">21</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;wt&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Û∞øé To Watch&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">entry</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file+headline</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/watch.org&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;TO WATCH:&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">22</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/tpl/tpl-towatch.txt&#34;</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">23</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">24</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;wd&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Û∞éÅ Watched&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">entry</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file+headline</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/watch.org&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;WATCHED:&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">25</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/tpl/tpl-watched.txt&#34;</span>) <span style="color:#517918">:prepend</span> <span style="color:#60add5">t</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">26</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">27</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;p&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;ÔÅÑ Plan&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">28</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;pd&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Û∞É∂ Daily Plan&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">plain</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/log.org&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">29</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/tpl/tpl-bod.txt&#34;</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">30</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">31</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;pr&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Û∞±Ñ Daily Review&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">plain</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/log.org&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">32</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/tpl/tpl-eod.txt&#34;</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">33</span><span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">34</span><span> (<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;pw&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;Û±õ° Weekly Review&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">plain</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/log.org&#34;</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">35</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;~/org/tpl/tpl-weekly.txt&#34;</span>))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">36</span><span> )
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">37</span><span> ))
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>Most thoughts throughout the day will be captured to my journal <em>log.org</em>. Tasks will be captured to the relevant todo file for refiling, tagging, scheduling and organisation. Each todo file (<em>personal/na/work</em>) has the following headings <em>INBOX:</em> and <em>NEXT:</em>. <em>INBOX</em> is where things sit until they have been prioritised, scheduled or tagged, by default they have one tag <em>:refile:</em> inherited from the heading making them easy to locate from agenda views. They get queued up under the <em>NEXT:</em> heading suggesting the order I want to complete things in. An agenda view search for the <em>:refile:</em> tag is then a unified inbox where I can sort tasks across the different areas.</p>
<h2 id="agenda-views">Agenda views</h2>
<p><img src="https://bledley.xyz/2025-06-25-how-i-use-org-mode-part-one/org-part-one-5.png" alt="Image 5"></p>
<p>I don&rsquo;t go to crazy with these. <em>C-c-TAB</em> or <em>C-c-a-a</em> brings up my default agenda view. A timeline of the current day that shows both events and scheduled tasks or deadlines. I leave the agenda view open and sticky in the background and have set up a key to toggle back and forth from whatever file I&rsquo;m in with <em>C-c 9</em></p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp"><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1</span><span><span style="color:#60a0b0;font-style:italic">;; Note this keybind requires that the agenda is already open in the background or it will just go to an empty buffer</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">2</span><span>(<span style="color:#bb60d5">global-set-key</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">kbd</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;C-c 9&#34;</span>) (<span style="color:#007020">lambda</span> ()
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">3</span><span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">interactive</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">4</span><span> (<span style="color:#007020;font-weight:bold">if</span> (<span style="color:#06287e">string=</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">buffer-name</span>) <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;*Org Agenda*&#34;</span>) (<span style="color:#bb60d5">previous-buffer</span>) (<span style="color:#bb60d5">switch-to-buffer</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;*Org Agenda*&#34;</span>))))
</span></span></code></pre></div><h2 id="the-daily-logorg">The daily log.org</h2>
<p><img src="https://bledley.xyz/2025-06-25-how-i-use-org-mode-part-one/org-part-one-6.png" alt="Image 6"></p>
<p>My main go to file during the day is my <em>log.org</em>. It&rsquo;s one long file that uses org-roam-dailies to create a date-tree journal with timestamped entries.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp"><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1</span><span><span style="color:#60a0b0;font-style:italic">;; Capture template for my daily log entries</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">2</span><span>(<span style="color:#007020;font-weight:bold">setq</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">org-roam-dailies-capture-templates</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">3</span><span> <span style="color:#666">&#39;</span>((<span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;d&#34;</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;default&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">entry</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">4</span><span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;* %&lt;%H:%M&gt; %?&#34;</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">5</span><span> <span style="color:#517918">:target</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">file+datetree</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;log.org&#34;</span> <span style="color:#bb60d5">week</span>)))
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">6</span><span> )
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>I have a keyboard shortcut that can quick capture an entry to the log from anywhere throughout the day. The default <em>&lsquo;org-roam-dailies&rsquo;</em> capture a separate file for each day and I started to find that counter productive. I would rarely ever look back on the individual files. With one long log I can quickly scan back over the past few days or weeks and information stays fresh unless I decide to fold a heading away or narrow the buffer to just today&rsquo;s date. Sometimes I create a little check list here at the beginning of the day for my main objectives, often I just ramble and capture fleeting thoughts throughout the day.</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" style="background-color:#f0f0f0;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"><code class="language-lisp" data-lang="lisp"><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1</span><span><span style="color:#60a0b0;font-style:italic">;; Keyboard shortcut to get to my daily log on today&#39;s date</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">2</span><span>(<span style="color:#bb60d5">global-set-key</span> (<span style="color:#bb60d5">kbd</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;C-c d&#34;</span>) <span style="color:#517918">&#39;org-roam-dailies-goto-today</span>)
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">3</span><span><span style="color:#60a0b0;font-style:italic">;; Alternative that uses leader key. Space d.</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">4</span><span>(<span style="color:#bb60d5">map!</span> <span style="color:#517918">:leader</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">5</span><span> <span style="color:#517918">:desc</span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;org-roam-dailies-goto-today&#34;</span>
</span></span><span style="display:flex;"><span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">6</span><span> <span style="color:#4070a0">&#34;d&#34;</span> <span style="color:#06287e">#&#39;</span><span style="color:#bb60d5">org-roam-dailies-goto-today</span>)
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>So that covers the basic foundation of my system in org mode. Hopefully, this starts to show why no other program, app or text editor comes close for me. Being able to have my notes, journal, tasks and calendar all under the one roof, whilst also being able to navigate my entire file system with Vim keybindings in Emacs is incredibly efficient and endlessly customizable. The reason I haven&rsquo;t gone explicitly in to all the keybinds and functions I use is that you will likely want to design your own based on the way you do things. We&rsquo;ve barely even scratched the surface of all the things Emacs and Org-mode is capable of here.</p>
<p>I keep my org-files in sync with my mobile with <a href="https://syncthing.net/">Syncthing</a> and access them there for some basic editing with <a href="https://orgro.org/">Orgro</a>. Of course we don&rsquo;t have all the features of Emacs there but I can quickly take a few notes to one of my files if needs be. My calendar events in <em>events.org</em> sync with <a href="https://github.com/dengste/org-caldav/blob/master/doc/org-caldav.org">org-cal-dav</a> to the <a href="https://www.fossify.org/">Fossify Calendar</a> app with <a href="https://www.davx5.com/">Davx5</a>.</p>
<p>A big part of my system not mentioned here is that I have some other folders related to note-taking with <a href="https://www.orgroam.com/">Org-Roam</a>. I feel my <a href="https://zettelkasten.de/introduction/">Zettelkasten</a> system is a separate one to my GTD related things although there can be some cross-over.</p>
<p>If you want to dive into my full messy <a href="https://github.com/bleds1/dotfiles/tree/main/.doom.d">Doom Emacs config</a> then you can find my dotfiles <a href="https://github.com/bleds1">here on Github</a>.. I push changes quite often and I will cover my Org-Roam note taking system in a future post.</p>
